cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.NE 

The paper presents a deep learning approach for predicting lung nodule malignancy from CT data, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The analysis of a large patient population and the high accuracy achieved by the model may also relate to the medical imaging (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning for classification tasks is a common theme in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
